snippet.textDisplay: I'm so bored with all of this rubbish.   why doesn't anyone ANYONE of these so called reporters ask the REAL hard hitting questions.  IF the oportuniety was to arise (see what I did there aka the dark knight rises....) if there was to be another Joker movie, how does Joaquin Pheonix feel about the idea of there being a second villian to wort alongside the Joker??  if so, Whom would Joaquin Pheonix prefer there to be by his side? and why?...  The penquinn perhalps?  The Riddler??    am spitballin now.. but what about clayface maybe?  or manbat???....    yeah okay so people may argue the fact that it's never good to rehash old sh*t and the idea of the concept may in fact and can pehalps possibly become stale..  but you do got to bare in mind and take into consideration about one of the all the time best beloved movie/comic book franchises of all time.  we have to keep the ball rolling here. we can't let it die.  we have to keep it going. we have to keep the wheels turning. I think there is so much more we can see yet.  I think this could quite possibly be one of the best storytellings we have yet to see.   I mean, don't forget about the boy wonder and alfred and the rest of the movie/comic book characters.  there is just so much they can still add.  what about harvey dent/2 face??   I think we could see such a more darker side to him that we have yet to see as well.  but this is just typical.  oh yh what the process to get in the mindset to become the Joker...  why is theee most common or only flippin question anyone can think to ask?  why?  do you want to become the demented twist sick in the head Joker yourself?   who would want too end up like him anyway?  ending up in a flippin mental institute after trying to blow up the whole world or whatever..   let's ask more practical questions shall we???    like for instants,  what was Joaquin's favorite part of the Joker movie?  and why?..  (actually scratch that last one I think I seen somewhere where he said the scene where Andy is in the Bathroom looking at himself and its when he does this interesting random small slow dance and that is when the Joker started to really become the Joker going threw the motions..  but I do think there are characters to be included and added.  Poison Ivy is still yet to appear in a remake or reboot. and same goes to Mr Freeze.  I grew up watching the animated batman chartoons and it was like, every episode, one after the next, it was always fresh and new and exciting to see whom else would end up being the next villian to try and take out the batman.  like, it was all the same stuff yet still managed to end up still being different. and that's how I see the Joker as.  we seen the 1966 joker. the jack nicloson joker.. the incredible heath ledger joker..  I mean.. it was so cool they finally made an origins Joker movie.  I really cannot wait to see where this might go next.  I do hope for more content.  but please try not to run this into the ground already.  the movie was so well done and producted and directed and produced.  am really happy with the outcome of the movie.   I enjoyed it so much I went back and saw it again.
